        How to make a double-sided bootable TOS disk.

1.  Format a double-sided disk by selecting a disk icon, then the 
    format option from the desktop menu.

2.  Click on the double-sided selector button.

3.  When  formatting  is finished,  select all the files on  your 
    original TOS disk and drag them to the newly formatted disk.

4.  Insert  the MichTron Utilites disk in the drive  and  double-
    click on the MUTIL.PRG file.

For the convenience of those not familiar with disks and TOS,  we 
have   provided  a  double-sided  boot  sector  on  the  MichTron 
Utilities disk.   Rather than try to figure out what bits need to 
be set,  you can just copy the information on track 1 sector 4 of 
the MichTron Utilities disk onto the boot sectors of your disk.

5.  After the MichTron Utilities opening screen  appears,  choose 
    track mode, then copy sectors from the Sector menu.

6.  Copy one sector from track 1 sector 4 of the MichTron disk to 
    track 0 sector 1 of the newly-created double-sided TOS disk.

7.  Reboot using your completed double-sided TOS disk.


