About volume labels


A slight bug in the way volume labels are handled by TOS prevents 
us  from  renaming  an existing volume label.  The  label  change 
option will add a new volume label to the disk.   The code in the 
program  will  handle  a rename when the TOS is  fixed,  so  this 
problem  will disappear in the future.   You need do  nothing  to 
modify this program; the code will allow you to directly change a 
volume  name  just as soon as you install a corrected version  of 
TOS.  (Not yet released as of November 8, 1985)

In  the meantime you must delete the existing volume label  on  a 
disk using the View Disk option.  To delete the label:

1.  Select View Disk.

2.  Next,  you must change the first letter of the volume name to 
    hex E5.   On a single-sided disk,  start at track 1 sector 3.  
    On a double-sided disk, start at track 0 sector 12.

3.  Move through the disk sectors until you see the volume name in 
    the ASCII display on the right-hand side.

4.  Change the first letter of the volume name to a hex "E5".  To 
    do so,  click on the first hex byte of the line,  then type "E5".  
    Click on Exit and Ok to delete the volume name.

5.  Select Change Label from the opening screen File menu to write 
    a new voloume name.

